						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in the compound of the Taluk office.</p>						

						<p>Kākatīya Pratāparudradēva Mahārāja, 1322 A.D.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1244 • • • • ., <hi rend="italic">Chaitra,</hi> śu. 5, Monday, corresponding to 1322 A.D., March 22.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to record a gift of land to god Kalikēśvaradēva of Kandukūru. Mentions Kāmaya Boppaniṁgāru, and Rudradēva, the latter probably as the donor.</p>						

						</summary>
